      <scopecontent id="aspace_e41c7f2128307bf9744d5983ee4ca619">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Collection of approximately 100 manuscript letters relating to the Bacon family of Worcester, Massachusetts, 1872-1944.</p>
         <p>Letters chiefly relate to siblings Francis Miles Bacon and Florence Mable Bacon Pierce and their time in Dakota Territory (now South Dakota), 1883-1893. These letters document Francis Bacon's farmwork, the domestic lives of his wife Mable "May" Louisa Sutton Bacon and sister Florence Pierce, and the general store of his brother-in-law Elmer Ellsworth Pierce, as well as death and disease, the weather, and the Panic of 1893.</p>
         <p>Other letters relate to Miles Bacon, Eliza C. Colburn Bacon, and Sarah Annie Bacon.</p>
         <p>A group of letters from 1944 are by Sarah "Sadie" Sutton to her neice Nellie May Bacon.</p>
      </scopecontent>
